<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747177>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 15. (a–c) Inversaria tubiporacea (Goldfuss); NHMUK D35836; Cretaceous, Maastrichtian, Valkenberg, east of Maastricht, Netherlands; (a) transversely fractured branch showing endozone (lower centre) surrounded by multizonal exozone; (b) detail of exozone showing regularly constricted autozooids;(c) operculum in an autozooidal chamber (arrowed).(d,e) Inversaria tuber Voigt and Williams; holotype, SMF 24524; late Maatrichtian, Kunrade, Limburg, Netherlands; (d) autozooids surrounding an avicularium; (e) new layer of growth developing on the colony surface. (f) Inversaria flabellula (von Hagenow); Cretaceous, early Maastrichtian, Rügen, Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Germany; SMF 24478; avicularium surrounded by autozooids. Scale bars: a = 2 mm; b, d, e = 1 mm; c = 200 µm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4747177/files/figure.png" .

